<HEADLINE>
FT  29 OCT 94 / Briefcase, Q&amp;A: Shares can't go into a Pep
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
I am a 25 per cent taxpayer, and I hold a modest portfolio of blue-chip
shares. Can I transfer Pounds 12,000 of these into a personal equity plan?
Apart from new issues, it is not possible to transfer stock into a Pep. You
would, therefore, have to sell Pounds 12,000 worth of shares and re-invest
the proceeds for yourself and your wife. (Murray Johnstone).
No legal responsibility can be accepted by the Financial Times for the
answers given in these columns. All enquiries will be answered by post as
soon as possible.
