<HEADLINE>
FT  29 OCT 94 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Black and white pepper prices were fully steady this week, reports Man
Producten. The week started with higher offers from India for black pepper
and the Malabar market has also been very firm. Short shippers continue to
eat away any carryover in Cochin. Whites prices for Indonesian supplies have
been rising quietly as Concern about the the effects of the dry weather has
increased. China is a seller but will soon run dry. The nutmegs and mace
market remained steady in origin, with limited offtake because most
industries are well covered until end this year. There were a few european
resellers taking profits by underquoting origins. When the current prices
survive this lull in the market we will certainly see a much firmer market
early next year, when coverage will be done for 1995. High grades of Cassia
are increasingly difficult to obtain.
</TEXT>
