<HEADLINE>
FT  29 OCT 94 / UK Company News: Reuters lifts sales 25% in quarter
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW BOLGER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Shares in Reuters Holdings rose by 30p to 477p after the financial
information and news group said its third quarter revenues rose 25 per cent
to Pounds 590m.
For the first nine months, sales grew by 23 per cent to Pounds 1.68bn, with
no material impact from exchange rate movements. Reuters, which started
giving quarterly statements this year, does not give profit figures.
Mr Peter Job, chief executive, said: 'Revenue continued to forge ahead
reflecting good business conditions as well as recent acquisitions. New
order rates for information products, though below the recent peaks we have
seen, were brisk.
'Electronic transaction products for the financial markets continued to be
the fastest growing part of the business.'
Acquisitions added Pounds 42m to revenue in the third quarter and Pounds 97m
in the nine months. Excluding acquisitions made since the beginning of 1993,
revenue growth was 17 per cent for the quarter and 16 per cent for the nine
months.
Sales growth by Instinet, the US-based equity brokerage service, and
Thamesway - the institutional broker acquired last November - contributed to
a 37 per cent rise to Pounds 138m in the quarter's overall transaction
product revenue.
Information management systems for dealing rooms increased sales 87 per cent
in the quarter, and over the nine months this product line's sales more than
doubled to Pounds 82m. This contributed to a rise of 20 per cent, to Pounds
1.19bn, in information products' revenue so far this year.
</TEXT>
