<HEADLINE>
FT  28 OCT 94 / London Stock Exchange: Hints of Hydro move
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By STEVE THOMPSON, PETER JOHN and JEFFREY BROWN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Rumours swept the market late yesterday that Scottish Hydro had called a
meeting of analysts for this morning, triggering speculation that it may
announce it will accept the terms of the recent regulatory review rather
than ask for a referral to the Monopolies and Mergers Commission.
Hydro shares underperformed the rest of the electricity stocks as the
rumours circulated, closing unchanged at 313p, contrasting with a 7 gain to
349p in Scottish Power and good gains in the English generators.
Hydro shares have underperformed the market by 10 per cent since the Offer
review last month, as some analysts have adopted the view that the package
would damage Hydro's dividend growth prospects.
