<HEADLINE>
FT  28 OCT 94 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The wool price rise continued and accelerated this week. Superfine merinos,
now coming up for auction more widely in Australia, met with good demand
from Italy, the leading world operator in this field. Prices for finer
merino fleece throughout the wool market recovery, now well over a year old,
have risen relatively more than other categories, and show no signs of
losing ground. With the wool market recovering healthily after a brief
setback towards the end of September, sales of Australian stockpile wool
have also improved, and the schedule fixed by the government is filled well
into 1995. Buying interest in the wool-using industry is not at present said
to be buoyant though steady business and good rates of activity continue.
The Australian Eastern states market indicator closed at 802 cents a kg,
compared with 762 a week ago.
</TEXT>
