FT  28 OCT 94 / International Company News: Dofasco doubles its quarterly
income
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MONTREAL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Dofasco, one of Canada's two biggest steel makers, nearly doubled pre-tax
profits in the third quarter with higher prices and surging demand for flat
rolled products for the car, appliance and pipeline industries, writes
Robert Gibbens in Montreal.
Sales rose 12 per cent to CDollars 565m and pre-tax profit was CDollars
57.2m (USDollars 42.5m), against CDollars 29.5m. But after special tax
factors, final net profit was CDollars 53.8m or 56 cents against Dollars 62m
or 70 cents a share a year earlier.
At the nine-month stage, net profits rose to CDollars 157.5m or CDollars
1.66, up from 56 per cent or 46 cents a share on sales of CDollars 1.65bn,
against CDollars 1.57bn.
