<HEADLINE>
FT  28 OCT 94 / UK Company News: Domino Printing
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Domino Printing Sciences, the ink-jet printer manufacturer, is broadening
its technology base with two acquisitions in the US.
The Cambridge-based group is paying Dollars 2.4m (Pounds 1.51m) cash for
Digi-Gear Systems, a private Illinois company supplying control systems. Its
book value is anticipated to be no more than Dollars 250,000.
In 1993 it achieved pre-tax profits of Dollars 100,000 on sales of Dollars
1.2m; sales and profits for 1994 were at higher levels, Domino said
yesterday.
Domino is also paying an initial Dollars 2.84m cash for certain assets of
Control Print, a trading division of Avery Dennison, which makes ink-jet
coding and marking systems. Book value amounts to Dollars 1m; it made an
operating profit of Dollars 651,000 in 1993 on sales of Dollars 9.1m.
</TEXT>
